<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="24Aug1938"><font color="red">24 August 1938</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Maurice Craig): You must have had an inspiring influence on my friend Eugene Jolas for the day after it he suddenly guessed the title of my book which nobody had succeeded in doing for the past sixteen years &hellip; The name of the song is &hellip; &lsquo;The Lord in His Mercy be kind (not good) to Belfast&rsquo;. I have been trying for years to get the air and words of it and also of &lsquo;Follow me up to Carlow&rsquo; </div>
